ARCHETYPE_Description_Cultist: The Cultists of Nurgle are individually no match for a Grey Knight, but they roam in packs and come armed with a variety of weapons
ARCHETYPE_Description_ApostatePreacher: The Apostate Preacher of Nurgle is a leader of cultists who can bestow vile boons upon his allies.
ARCHETYPE_Description_Poxwalker: These poor infected have been cursed by one of Nurgle's plagues: The walking pox.  Although physically weak, their sheer numbers can overwhelm.
ARCHETYPE_Description_PlagueMarine: These corrupted Astartes have dedicated their souls to the service of the Chaos God Nurgle.  With their disgusting power armour bloated with plague and corruption, they are highly resilient and immune to pain.
ARCHETYPE_Description_PlagueChampion: A commander of the Plague Marines, this Champion can issue ruthless orders that provide valuable combat Boons to his allies.
ARCHETYPE_Description_PlagueBearer: Footsoldiers of Nurgle's legions, the Plaguebearer is a lesser Daemon who wields a Plaguesword that can strike vile Afflictions on its targets.
ARCHETYPE_Description_PlagueRidden: A sergeant amongt legions of Plaguebearers, this disgusting creature can spew vile afflictions on its enemies and bestow the gift of Nurgle's mutations on its allies.
ARCHETYPE_Description_Nurgling: The Mites of Nurgle often accompany the Great Unclean One's into battle as a mischievous retinue.  Small and difficult to target, they are only dangerous when they appear in hordes.
ARCHETYPE_Description_Helbrute: This nightmarish mockery of an Astartes Dreadnought is an unstable, but powerful force armed with a variety of weaponry and strong armour.  Its greatest strength is its rage, which it unleashes in retaliation on its enemies.
ARCHETYPE_Description_BlightlordTerminat: The Blightlord Terminators are an elite cadre of the Death Guard, armed with a powerful Reaper Autocannon for long-range suppression, while still formidable in close range wielding a Bubotic Axe.
ARCHETYPE_Description_BlightlordChampion: The Champion is the most elite of the Blightlord Terminator units, armed with a Flail of Corruption and heavy shield, they will rush at the head of the vanguard, terrifying their foes.
ARCHETYPE_Description_FoetidBloatDrone: This floating Daemon Engine of Nurgle is armed with a heavy Frag Missile Launcher that can unleash a deadly barrage over a wide area from above.
ARCHETYPE_Description_ChaosSpawn: A fearsome foe, the Chaos Spawn is a mindless abomination afflicted with a wide range of Nurgle's mutations.  Its deadly claw can be used to pin and execute a Grey Knight if left to its own devices.
ARCHETYPE_Description_MyphiticBlightHaul: This tracked Daemon Engine provides the Death Guard with heavy firepower when needed.  It is equipped with a fearsome close-range Multi-Melta and long-range Frag Missile Launcher.
ARCHETYPE_Description_GreatUncleanOne: We have found him, the Reaper of the Poxus Strain: Aeger the Benevolent.  A Greater Daemon embodying corruption and disease, he is known to consort with a small army of Nurgling "Nephews".
ARCHETYPE_Description_PlagueHulk: We have located the Reaper of the Necrosus Strain: Morgellus the Corroded Prince.  This Plague Hulk of Nurgle is a fearsome avatar of rust and rot, equipped with an impressive array of firepower.
ARCHETYPE_Description_Malathian: Malathian the Harvester, Reaper of the Mortus Strain, has been located below.  As a vile avatar of fear and death, he leads a ceaseless army of Plaguebearers and inflicts curses through his Effigies of corruption.
ARCHETYPE_Description_ChaosKnight: Our Prognosticars sense the presence of Cruciatus the Generous below: A Knight Desecrator corrupted to the service of Nurgle, and now Reaper of the Dolorus Strain.  His armaments far outweigh the capabilities of even our Knights.
ARCHETYPE_Description_Munificus: We have discovered the location of the Greater Chaos Spawn: Munificus the Undying, Reaper of the Tentarus Strain.  This creature is constantly evolving and seems to be capable of healing at an astonishing rate.
ARCHETYPE_Description_UnknownArchetype: Our Prognosticars have augured that we will face minions of Chaos on the planet's surface.  If we Attune a Prognosticar to this system, they will be able to tell us more.
BODY_PART_MUNIFICUS_HEAD_DESC: The target can no longer use [b:Bile Spray].
BODY_PART_MUNIFICUS_DISEASEDTALON_DESC: The target cannot attack with its [b:Diseased Talon].
BODY_PART_MUNIFICUS_NEEDLER_TITLE: The target cannot attack with its [b:Needler].
HELBRUTE_TORSO_ON_HIT_TORSO_DESCRIPTION: Expose the target's armour to reveal a vulnerable Target Point.
CLASS_Justicar_Description: The Justicar gains [g:+{armourBonus}] [b:Armour] with their [b:Aegis Shield] ability.
CLASS_Apothecary_Description: The Apothecary can equip the [b:Narthecium], giving them access to the [b:Battlefield Medicine] ability.
CLASS_Purgator_Description: The Purgator can equip the [b:Psycannon], [b:Psilencer] and [b:Incinerator] Ranged Weapons.
CLASS_Paladin_Description: The Paladin has access to the [b:Storm Shield] and can only equip [b:Terminator Armour]
CLASS_Librarian_Description: The Librarian gains [g:+{willpowerAmount}] Max WP starting from Rank 1 and can only equip [b:Terminator Armour].
CLASS_Chaplain_Description: The Chaplain gains [g:+1] [b:Armour] by default and can only equip [b:Terminator Armour].
CLASS_Purifier_Description: The Purifier can equip the [b:Psycannon], [b:Psilencer] or [b:Incinerator], and is immune to damage effects from [b:Hazards].
